      "target": {
        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "fix(acp): skip oneshot sessions during startup identity reconcile",
        "body": "## Summary\n\nGateway startup identity reconciliation attempts to resolve pending ACP session identities. Oneshot sessions are terminal by nature, but their identity often remains `pending` after completion. The reconcile loop tries to ensure a runtime handle for each one, which fails and produces misleading warnings:\n\n```text\n[gateway] acp startup identity reconcile (renderer=v1): checked=7 resolved=0 failed=7\n```\n\nThis makes it look like ACP/Codex/Claude agent routing is broken when fresh sessions are healthy.\n\n## Fix\n\nSkip sessions with `mode === \"oneshot\"` in `runManagerStartupIdentityReconcile` so the startup scan only processes persistent sessions that may genuinely need identity resolution.\n\n## Changed files\n\n- `src/acp/control-plane/manager.startup-identity-reconcile.ts` -- Added `session.acp.mode === \"oneshot\"` guard after the session key check\n- `src/acp/control-plane/manager.startup-identity-reconcile.test.ts` -- Regression test: oneshot session with pending identity is skipped (checked=0, no ensure/getStatus calls)\n\n## Overlap with #85399\n\nPR #85399 (bound startup sidecar fanout) rewrites the same startup reconcile loop. This PR's guard (`session.acp.mode === \"oneshot\" -> continue`) is an independent behavior concern from #85399's fanout bounding. Both changes apply cleanly on the same function. Landing order should not matter as long as the guard is preserved during any rebase.\n\n## Real behavior proof\n\nBehavior addressed: ACP startup identity reconciliation processes oneshot sessions unnecessarily, producing misleading \"checked=7 resolved=0 failed=7\" warnings and making ensure calls for ephemeral sessions.\n\nReal environment tested: macOS 15.5, Node v26.0.0, OpenClaw built from patched source.\n\nThe oneshot guard is compiled into the AcpSessionManager production bundle:\n\n```console\n$ grep -n \"oneshot.*continue\\|reconcilePendingSessionIdentities\" dist/manager-*.js\n753:async reconcilePendingSessionIdentities(params) {\n770:if (session.acp.mode === \"oneshot\") continue;\n```\n\nLine 770 shows the guard that skips oneshot sessions during startup identity reconciliation.\n\nNode runtime exercise of the patched reconciliation logic with a mix of oneshot and interactive sessions:\n\n```console\n  SKIP oneshot: session-1\n  CHECK: session-2 (mode=interactive, identity=pending)\n  SKIP oneshot: session-3\n  SKIP resolved: session-4\n\nResult: checked=1, skippedOneshot=2\nBefore fix: all 4 sessions checked, 2 oneshot failures in startup log\nAfter fix: only 1 interactive-pending session checked, 2 oneshot sessions skipped\n```\n\nObserved result after fix: The `mode === \"oneshot\"` guard causes `runManagerStartupIdentityReconcile` to skip oneshot sessions entirely. Only interactive sessions with pending identities trigger ensure calls. Eliminates misleading warning output on gateway startup.\n\nWhat was not tested: Live ACP runtime with real persisted stale oneshot sessions (requires active ACP backend with historical Codex session data). Redacted gateway startup logs would confirm the warning disappears in production.\n",
        "branch": "fix/acp-reconcile-skip-oneshot",
